= \n|timezone_DST           = \n|utc_offset_DST         = \n|coordinates            = {{coord|44|17|51|N|20|15|50|E|region:RS|display=inline,title}}\n|elevation_footnotes    =  <!--for references: use <ref> </ref> tags-->\n|elevation_m            = 146\n|elevation_ft           = \n<!-- Area/postal codes & others -------->\n|postal_code_type       =  <!-- enter ZIP code, Postcode, Post code, Postal code... -->\n|postal_code            =11561\n|area_code              =011\n|blank_name             =\n|blank_info             =\n|blank1_name            =\n|blank1_info            =\n|website                =\n|footnotes              = \n}} \n\n'''Dudovica''' ({{lang-sr|\u0414\u0443\u0434\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0446\u0430}}) is a small town in the [[Lazarevac]] municipality in the [[Belgrade District]] of [[Serbia]]. It was seat of a municipality abolished in the 1960s and added to the municipality of Lazarevac.\n\n==Demographics==\n{{Historical populations\n| type = \n| percentages = pagr\n|1948|854 |1953|922 |1961|923 |1971|895 |1981|818 |1991|828 |2002|777 |2011|701\n| source = \n}}\nAccording to the 2011 census results, the village has 701 inhabitants.\n\n===Ethnic groups===\nThe ethnic composition of the village (as of 2002 census):\n* [[Serbs]]: 769 - 98,97%\n* [[Yugoslavs]]: 4 - 0,51%\n* [[Montenegrins (ethnic group)|Montenegrins]]: 3 - 0,38%\n* [[Romanians]]: 1 - 0,12%\n* Unknown: 0 - 0,0%\n\n==Economy==\n\nDudovica is known as the breeding area of the [[mangalica]] pigs.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.politika.rs/sr/clanak/254840/Ruralni-Beograd-dve-trecine-prestonice|author=Dimitrije Bukvi\u0107|title= Ruralni Beograd - dve tre\u0107ine prestonice|date=14 April 2013| publisher= [[Politika]]|language=Serbian}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n19 people from Dudovica were killed in the Jasenovac Camp in the World War II. All were ethnic Serbs.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cp13.heritagewebdesign.com/~lituchy/victim_search.php?field%3Dorigin%26searchtype%3Dcontains%26data%3Ddudovica |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2008-11-03 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110711163926/https://cp13.heritagewebdesign.com/~lituchy/victim_search.php?field=origin&searchtype=contains&data=dudovica |archivedate=2011-07-11 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Dudovica}}\n*[http://www.maplandia.com/serbia-and-montenegro/srbija/dudovica/ Satellite map at Maplandia.com]\n\n[[Category:Suburbs of Belgrade]]\n[[Category:\u0160umadija]]\n[[Category:Lazarevac]]\n\n{{BelgradeRS-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n<!--See the Table at Infobox Settlement for all fields and descriptions of usage-->\n<!-- Basic info  ---------------->\n|official_name          = Dudovica\n|other_name             = \n|native_name            = \u0414\u0443\u0434\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0446\u0430\n|nickname               = \n|settlement_type        = Village\n|motto                  = \n<!-- images and maps  ----------->\n|image_skyline          = Ulaz u Dudovicu.jpg\n|imagesize              = \n|image_caption          = Entrance to Dudovica\n|image_flag             = \n|flag_size              =\n|image_seal             = \n|seal_size              =\n|image_shield           = \n|shield_size            =\n|image_blank_emblem     =\n|blank_emblem_type      =\n|blank_emblem_size      =\n|image_map              = \n|mapsize                = \n|map_caption            = \n|image_map1             = \n|mapsize1               = \n|map_caption1           = \n|image_dot_map          =\n|dot_mapsize            =\n|dot_map_caption        =\n|dot_x =  |dot_y =\n|pushpin_map            = Serbia<!-- the name of a location map as per http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Template:Location_map -->\n|pushpin_label_position =bottom\n|pushpin_map_caption    =Location in Serbia\n<!-- Location ------------------>\n|subdivision_type       = Country\n|subdivision_name       = {{flag|Serbia}}\n|subdivision_type1      = Region\n|subdivision_name1      