"text-align:left;\"|[[Nikola Drin\u010di\u0107]]\n|2007\u20132014\n|'''1''' (33)\n|-\n|-\n|}\n\n==Competition history==\nMontenegro have participated in five qualification rounds for World Cup or European Championship tournaments. Montenegro have never qualified, and their biggest success was reaching the play-offs for [[UEFA Euro 2012|Euro 2012]].<br>\nMontenegro first tried to qualify for the [[2010 FIFA World Cup|2010 World Cup]] in [[South Africa]], but they finished fifth in their [[2010 FIFA World Cup qualification \u2013 UEFA Group 8|group]]. They had more success in the [[UEFA Euro 2012 qualifying|Euro 2012 qualifiers]], when they finished second in their group to reach the [[UEFA Euro 2012 qualifying play-offs|play-offs]], but lost to the [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic]].<br>\nIn the [[2014 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)|qualifiers]] for the [[2014 FIFA World Cup|2014 World Cup]], Montenegro finished third, and two years later, in the [[UEFA Euro 2016 qualifying|qualifiers]] for [[UEFA Euro 2016|Euro 2016]], they finished fourth in their group. They again finished third in their [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)|2018 World Cup qualifying group]]. Worst performance came in the qualifiers for [[UEFA Euro 2020|Euro 2020]], as Montenegro finished last-placed in the group without single victory.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! Competition\n! G\n! W\n! D\n! L\n! GF\n! GA\n! GD\n|-\n|[[FIFA World Cup]] qualifiers\n|'''30'''\n| 10\n| 10\n| 10\n| 47\n| 43\n| +4\n|-\n|[[UEFA European Championship]] qualifiers\n|'''28'''\n| 6\n| 8\n| 14\n| 20\n| 45\n| -25\n|-\n|[[UEFA Nations League]]\n|'''6'''\n| 2\n| 1\n| 3\n| 7\n| 6\n| +1\n|-\n|Friendly games\n|'''40'''\n| 16\n| 9\n| 15\n| 50\n| 48\n| +2\n|-\n|'''OVERALL'''\n|'''104'''\n| '''34'''\n| '''28'''\n| '''42'''\n| '''124'''\n| '''142'''\n| '''-18'''\n|}\n''Updated: March 03, 2020''\n\n===[[FIFA World Cup]]===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-