Sons|isbn=0585423946|lccn=2001046960|oclc=50739343|accessdate=2019-09-19|via=[[Internet Archive]]}}\n**{{cite web |last=Corrigan |first=Mary Beth |date=April 2003 |title=Benjamin Banneker: Fabled Genius Considered\": Review of Cerami, Charles A. (2002), ''Benjamin Banneker: Surveyor, Astronomer, Publisher, Patriot'', New York: John Wiley & Sons ''\"H-Net Reviews in the Humanities & Social Sciences:  H-Net Maryland'' |url=http://www.h-net.org/reviews/showpdf.php?id=7440 |work=H-Net: Humanities & Social Sciences Online |location=[[Lansing, Michigan]] |publisher=MATRIX: The Center for Humane Arts, Letters and Social Sciences Online: Department of History: [[Michigan State University]] |accessdate=2013-07-08 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120905204059/http://www.h-net.org/reviews/showpdf.php?id=7440 |archivedate=2012-09-05}}\n* {{cite book|url=https://archive.org/stream/freedmensbook01chil#page/n27/mode/1up|title=Benjamin Banneker|work=The Freedmen's Book|last=Child|first=Lydia Maria|authorlink=Lydia Maria Child|pages=14\u201323|year=1865|publisher=Ticknor and Fields|location=[[Boston]], [[Massachusetts]]|lccn=12002981|oclc=708562|accessdate=2018-05-28|via=[[Internet Archive]]}}\n* {{cite journal|last=Conway|first=Moncure D.|author-link=Moncure D. Conway|url=https://babel.hathitrust.org/cgi/pt?id=hvd.32044103018420;view=1up;seq=89|title=Benjamin Banneker, the Negro Astronomer|pages=79\u201384|volume=11|date=January 1863|number=63|journal=[[The Atlantic|The Atlantic Monthly]]|location=[[Boston]], [[Massachusetts]]|publisher=Ticknor & Fields|via=[[HathiTrust|HathiTrust Digital Library]]|accessdate=2019-03-21}}\n* {{cite book |last=Crew |first=Harvey W., Webb, William Bensing, Wooldridge, John |year=1892 |url=https://books.google.com/?id=5Q81AAAAIAAJ&&pg=PA87#v=onepage&q&f=false |work=Centennial History of the City of Washington, D.C. |publisher=United Brethren Publishing House |place=Dayton, Ohio |title=IV. \"Permanent Capital Site Selected\"|page=87|lccn=06028029|oclc=2843595 |accessdate=2009-05-07|via=[[Google Books]]}}\n* {{cite book |last=Jusserand|first=Jean Jules|author-link=Jean Jules Jusserand |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=u2MUAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA137#v=onepage&q&f=false |work=With Americans of Past and Present Days||oclc=1075914 |title=Major L'Enfant and the Federal City |location=New York |publisher=[[Charles Scribner's Sons]] |pages=137\u2013195 |year=1916 |accessdate=2011-08-15 |via=[[Google Books]]}}\n* {{cite book|last=Latrobe|first=John H. B., Esq.|url=https://archive.org/details/memoirbenjaminb00socigoog/page/n7/mode/1up|title=Memoir of Benjamin Banneker: Read before the Maryland Historical Society at the Monthly Meeting, May 1, 1845|location=Baltimore, Maryland|publisher=Printed by John D. Toy|year=1845|lccn=rc01003345|oclc=85791076|accessdate=February 29, 2020|via=[[Internet Archive]]}}\n* {{cite book|last=Morrison|first=Hugh Alexander|url=https://archive.org/details/preliminarycheck00morr|title=Preliminary Check List of American Almanacs: 1639-1800|work=Library of Congress|year=1907|publisher=[[United States Government Publishing Office|Government Printing Office]]|oclc=577096527|lccn=06035021|location=Washington, D.C.|accessdate=December 31, 2018|via=[[Internet Archive]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181231033020/https://books.google.com/books?id=7JRJ-AXbTTMC&printsec=frontcover&source=gbs_ge_summary_r&cad=0|archive-date=December 31, 2018|url-status=dead}}\n* {{cite journal |last=Stewart |first=John |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=GgULOzNSafMC&pg=PA48#v=onepage&q&f=false |title=Early Maps and Surveyors of the City of Washington, D.C. |year=1899 |journal=Records of the Columbia Historical Society |publisher=[[Historical Society of Washington, D.C.|Columbia Historical Society]] |location=Washington, D.C. |volume=2 |pages=48\u201371 |issn=0897-9049 |oclc=40326234 |accessdate=2011-08-15 |via=[[Google Books]]}}\n* {{cite book |url=https://archive.org/details/bub_gb_D_ZJBxoCYeAC_2 |title=Standard History of the City of Washington From a Study of the Original Sources |last=Tindall |first=William |location=Knoxville, Tennessee |publisher=H. W. Crew and Company |year=1914 |lccn=14013663|oclc=7059152 |accessdate=2013-01-31 |via=[[Internet Archive]]}}\n* {{cite book |url=https://archive.org/details/sketchoflifeofbe00tyso/page/n4/mode/1up|title=A sketch of the life of Benjamin Banneker: from notes taken in 1836: read by J. Saurin Norris, before the Maryland Historical Society, October 5th, 1854 |first=Martha Ellicott |last=Tyson |location=Baltimore, Maryland|publisher=Printed for the Maryland Historical Society by John D. Toy |lccn=rc01003357|oclc=85794847|accessdate=2015-04-24|via=[[Internet Archive]]}}\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category-inline|Benjamin Banneker}}\n\n{{Portal bar|Biography|History|United States|Maryland}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Banneker, Mythology and legacy of Benjamin}}\n[[Category:African-American culture]]\n[[Category:American folklore]]\n[[Category:Misconceptions]]\n[[Category:Urban legends]]\n[[Category:Legacies by person]]\n", "name_user": "Corker1", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eBanneker's clock:editorial change", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mythology_of_Benjamin_Banneker"}
{"title_page": "Pod Save America", "text_new": "{{short description|American political podcast}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=June 2018}}\n{{Infobox Podcast\n |show_name     = Pod Save America\n |image         = Pod_save_america_logo.jpg\n |caption       = \n |alt           =\n |updates       = Twice weekly\n |runtime       = 41\u201396 minutes\n |country       = United States\n |language      = English\n |presenter     = {{ubl|[[Jon Favreau (speechwriter)|Jon Favreau]]|[[Daniel Pfeiffer]]|[[Jon Lovett]]|[[Tommy Vietor]]}}\n |first_aired   = {{Start date|2017|1}}\n |last_aired    = \n |num_episodes  =\n |audio_format  =\n |website       = {{URL|https://crooked.com/podcast-series/pod-save-america/}}\n |provider      = [[Cadence13]]\n |genre         = Political\n}}\n\n'''''Pod Save America''''' is an American [[Progressivism in the United States|progressive]] [[political podcast]] produced and distributed by [[Crooked Media]]. The podcast debuted in January 2017 and airs twice weekly, with the Monday edition hosted by former [[Barack Obama]] staffers [[Jon Favreau (speechwriter)|Jon Favreau]], [[Tommy Vietor]], and [[Jon Lovett]], and the Thursday edition by Favreau and [[Daniel Pfeiffer|Dan Pfeiffer]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2017/jan/18/podcasts-trump-presidency-political-left-right-alt-right|title=Pod save America: 12 podcasts to get you through the Trump presidency|first=Craille Maguire|last=Gillies|date=January 18, 2017|publisher=[[The Guardian]]}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/03/20/business/media/rutenberg-trump-opposition-pod-save-america.html|title=Opposition and a Shave: Former Obama Aides Counter Trump|last=Rutenberg|first=Jim|date=March 20, 2017|work=The New York Times|access-date=March 22, 2017|issn=0362-4331}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.gq.com/story/pod-save-america-colbert|title=The Pod Save America Guys Have Some Ideas About What President Obama Should Do Next|last=Willis|first=Jay|date=April 6, 2017|work=GQ|access-date=June 11, 2017|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.newsweek.com/crooked-media-fights-trump-pod-save-america-jon-favreau-jon-lovett-tommy-570695|title=Crooked Media Fights Trump with \"Pod Save America\"|date=March 26, 2017|work=Newsweek|access-date=June 11, 2017}}</ref>\n\nIt is the flagship podcast of [[Crooked Media]], a media company founded by Favreau, Vietor, and Lovett.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2017/01/09/the-keepin-it-1600-guys-launch-crooked-media-to-counter-trump|title=The 'Keepin' It 1600' Guys Launch Crooked Media to Counter Trump|last=Wilstein|first=Matt|date=January 9, 2017|work=The Daily Beast|access-date=January 3, 2018}}</ref> The show averages more than 3.5 million listeners an episode, and has been downloaded more than 120 million times as of November 2017.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/11/22/magazine/the-voices-in-blue-americas-head.html?smid=tw-nytimes&smtyp=cur|title=The Voices in Blue America's Head|last=Zengerle|first=Jason|access-date=November 22, 2017|language=en}}</ref> \n\nFour ''Pod Save America'' one-hour [[HBO]] TV specials aired in fall 2018 to cover the [[United States elections, 2018|U.S. midterm elections]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hbo.com/hbo-news/pod-save-america-podcast-specials|title=- HBO Announces Pod Save America Podcast Specials|website=HBO}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/pod-save-america-getting-hbo-treatment-election-specials-1083148|title='Pod Save America' Getting HBO Treatment With Election Specials|website=hollywoodreporter.com}}</ref> Crooked Media also films the podcasts and releases them on their [[YouTube]] channel.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCKRoXz3hHAu2XL_k3Ef4vJQ/videos|title=Crooked Media|website=YouTube|language=en|access-date=2019-04-08}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nThe podcast debuted in January 2017 as a successor to ''[[Keepin' it 1600]]'', a political podcast produced by [[Bill Simmons]]' [[The Ringer (website)|The Ringer]] and hosted by Favreau, Vietor, Lovett, and Pfeiffer which ran from March to December 2016. ''Pod Save America'' maintained the basic format of its predecessor.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/keeping-1600-podcasts-obama-alums-launch-new-show-crooked-media-company-961556|title='Keeping It 1600' Podcast's Obama Alums Launch New Show and 'Crooked Media' Company|work=The Hollywood Reporter|access-date=January 3, 2018|language=en}}</ref>\n\nIn an interview with [[Recode]]'s [[Kara Swisher]], the hosts have stated that, rather than continue the previous podcast, the election of [[Donald Trump]] as [[President of the United States|President]] of the [[United States]] spurred them to create a progressive media company with a network of podcasts. Their goal is to inform their millions of fans and viewers that trust them as a reliable source.\n\n== Tour ==\nCrooked Media took the podcast on its first live tour, ''Pod Tours America,'' in the fall of 2017. Live shows were recorded and released as podcasts.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://consequenceofsound.net/2017/08/pod-save-america-announces-nationwide-tour/|title=Pod Save America announces nationwide tour|date=August 16, 2017|work=Consequence of Sound|access-date=January 3, 2018|language=en-US}}</ref> An international tour, ''Pod Tours the World'', was announced for 2018, with live shows in Stockholm, Oslo, Amsterdam, and London.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.list.co.uk/article/97781-pod-save-america-and-lovett-or-leave-it-are-coming-to-london-in-january-heres-how-to-get-tickets/|title=Pod Save America and Lovett or Leave It are coming to London in January, here's how to get tickets|date=December 1, 2017|work=The List|access-date=January 3, 2018|language=en-GB}}</ref>\n\n==Content==\nThe podcast typically covers recent news items relating to politics, including the Trump administration, the US government and the Democratic Party, as well as progressive grassroots activism.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2017/mar/19/the-week-in-radio-pod-save-america-the-long-view-podcast|title=The week in radio: Pod Save America; The Long View|last=Sawyer|first=Miranda|date=March 19, 2017|work=The Observer|access-date=January 3, 2018|language=en-GB|issn=0029-7712}}</ref>\n\nThe show typically features interviews with politicians, activists and journalists, including Obama's last interview as president.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2017/jan/26/pod-save-america-the-podcast-that-won-obamas-last-interview|title=Pod Save America \u2013 the podcast that won Obama's last interview|last=Verdier|first=Hannah|date=January 26, 2017|work=The Guardian|access-date=January 3, 2018|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref> Other guests have included [[Hillary Clinton]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/us-politics/hillary-clinton-trump-clear-present-threat-pod-save-america-podcast-interview-a7943726.html|title=Hillary Clinton says Donald Trump 'is a clear and present danger to America'|date=September 12, 2017|work=The Independent|access-date=January 3, 2018|language=en-GB}}</ref> and senators [[Bernie Sanders]], [[Elizabeth Warren]], [[Cory Booker]], [[Kamala Harris]], and [[Chris Murphy (Connecticut politician)|Chris Murphy]]. They have interviewed several former [[2020 Democratic Party presidential primaries|2020 Democratic Presidential candidates]], including Sanders, Booker, Harris, [[Beto O'Rourke]], [[Andrew Yang]], [[Pete Buttigieg]], [[Marianne Williamson]], and [[Amy Klobuchar]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://crooked.com/podcast-series/pod-save-america/|title=Pod Save America Archives|website=Crooked Media|language=en-US|access-date=2019-06-24}}</ref> Guests are often referred to as \"friends of the pod\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news.vice.com/en_ca/article/a3jadk/podcasts-are-becoming-the-lefts-right-wing-talk-radio|title=Podcasts are becoming the left's right-wing talk radio|work=VICE News|access-date=January 3, 2018|language=en}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Pod Save America (30363).jpg|thumb|Favreau, Vietor, and guest [[Seth Meyers]] at a live taping at [[Radio City Music Hall]]]]\n\n== Reception ==\nThe show averages more than 1.5 million listeners an episode, and had been downloaded more than 120 million times by November 2017.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nThe ''[[The New York Times|New York Times]]'' described the podcast as \"one of the big breakout hits of the nascent resistance movement\",<ref name=\":1\" /> and \"the left's answer to conservative talk radio... with a shoestring budget and no organizational backing, its hosts seem to have created something that liberals have spent almost two decades, and hundreds of millions of dollars, futilely searching for\".<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nThe ''[[San Francisco Chronicle]]'' called it \"one of the nation's most popular podcasts\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.sfchronicle.com/politics/article/Pod-Save-America-about-to-take-its-next-step-12418780.php|title='Pod Save America' about to take its next step|work=San Francisco Chronicle|access-date=January 3, 2018}}</ref> ''[[GQ]]'' called it one of the \"most popular strategies for coping with the looming death of the republic\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.gq.com/story/pod-save-america-colbert|title=The 'Pod Save America' Guys Gave Donald Trump His Best, Weirdest Nickname Yet|last=Willis|first=Jay|date=April 6, 2017|work=GQ|access-date=January 3, 2018|language=en}}</ref>\n\n''[[Newsweek]]'' wrote that the show's hosts \"do something far more rare [than political analysis], which is to make politics entertaining and even fun, without ever downplaying what they see as the threat posed to American democracy by the man elected to defend it.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.newsweek.com/crooked-media-fights-trump-pod-save-america-jon-favreau-jon-lovett-tommy-570695|title=How the Crooked Media trio is taking on Donald Trump with \"Pod Save America\"|date=March 26, 2017|work=Newsweek|access-date=January 3, 2018|language=en}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Pod Save the World]]\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|https://crooked.com/podcast-series/pod-save-america/}}\n\n{{Crooked Media}}\n\n[[Category:2017 podcast debuts]]\n[[Category:Audio podcasts]]\n[[Category:Political podcasts]]\n[[Category:Crooked Media]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American political podcast}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=June 2018}}\n{{Infobox Podcast\n |show_name     = Pod Save America\n |image         = Pod_save_america_logo.jpg\n |caption       = \n |alt           =\n |updates       = Twice weekly\n |runtime       = 41\u201396 minutes\n |country       = United States\n |language      = English\n |presenter     = {{ubl|[[Jon Favreau (speechwriter)|Jon Favreau]]|[[Daniel Pfeiffer]]|[[Jon Lovett]]|[[Tommy Vietor]]}}\n |first_aired   = {{Start date|2017|1}}\n |last_aired    = \n |num_episodes  =\n |audio_format  =\n |website       = {{URL|https://crooked.com/podcast-series/pod-save-america/}}\n |provider      = [[Cadence13]]\n |genre         = Political\n}}\n\n'''''Pod Save America''''' is an American [[Progressivism in the United States|progressive]] [[political podcast]] produced and distributed by [[Crooked Media]]. The podcast debuted in January 2017 and airs twice weekly, with the Monday edition hosted by former [[Barack Obama]] staffers [[Jon Favreau (speechwriter)|Jon Favreau]], [[Tommy Vietor]], and [[Jon Lovett]], and the Thursday edition by Favreau and [[Daniel Pfeiffer|Dan Pfeiffer]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2017/jan/18/podcasts-trump-presidency-political-left-right-alt-right|title=Pod save America: 12 podcasts to get you through the Trump presidency|first=Craille Maguire|last=Gillies|date=January 18, 2017|publisher=[[The Guardian]]}}</ref><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite news|url=htt